06:04.097 --> 06:06.099
‐Balki, can I ask a question?
‐Sure.

06:06.132 --> 06:10.403
When you negotiate on Mypos
what exactly is your goal?

06:12.839 --> 06:14.908
Well, our goal is for each side

06:14.941 --> 06:16.577
to agree on a fair price

06:16.610 --> 06:18.545
and then party till we drop.

06:21.081 --> 06:23.550
♪ Hey beegy... ♪

06:23.584 --> 06:24.585
‐Balki.
‐Yes.

06:24.618 --> 06:28.154
Forget the Hongi Bongi
ritual of purification.

06:28.188 --> 06:29.756
But, cousin,
I‐I really have to‐‐

06:29.790 --> 06:33.694
Balki, this is not Mypos.
It’s America.

06:33.727 --> 06:34.995
Sit down.

06:39.800 --> 06:42.035
Balki, when Americans negotiate

06:42.068 --> 06:44.437
they don’t, they don’t care
about a fair price.

06:44.470 --> 06:47.140
All they care about is getting
as much as they can

06:47.173 --> 06:49.943
for as little as possible.
You see?

06:49.976 --> 06:51.678
Now‐now the very first Americans

06:51.712 --> 06:54.014
negotiated a deal
with the Indians.

06:54.047 --> 06:56.082
They gave them $24
worth of beads

06:56.116 --> 06:58.552
for the island of Manhattan.

06:58.585 --> 07:00.587
And now Americans
are making billions of dollars

07:00.621 --> 07:03.423
by selling the same island
to the Japanese.

07:09.262 --> 07:11.765
These beads...

07:11.798 --> 07:14.668
...were they real
or synthetic?

07:17.137 --> 07:19.606
Balki, I think you’re going
to have to find someone

07:19.640 --> 07:23.243
to help you with American
negotiating techniques.

07:23.276 --> 07:25.846
You’re right.

07:25.879 --> 07:29.916
Cousin, would you be my official
negotiating adviser?

07:29.950 --> 07:31.885
Well, I’d be honored.

07:31.918 --> 07:33.620
There’s a ceremony.

07:35.021 --> 07:37.791
I’d rather pass on that.

07:37.824 --> 07:39.593
‐It’s important.
‐Is it necessary?

07:39.626 --> 07:41.962
‐It’s mandatory.
‐Okay.

07:41.995 --> 07:44.598
Let’s get the humiliation
over with.

07:46.767 --> 07:48.969
Cousin Larry Appleton

07:49.002 --> 07:54.140
you are my official
negotiating adviser.

07:59.913 --> 08:02.516
‐That’s it?
‐That’s it. Got any advice?

08:15.796 --> 08:17.631
Mr. Stanhouse will be
with you shortly.

08:17.664 --> 08:18.665
Thank you.

08:31.177 --> 08:33.679
Cousin, this room is beautiful.

08:33.714 --> 08:35.115
It’s even more beautiful

08:35.148 --> 08:36.750
than the room at the Holiday Inn

08:36.783 --> 08:38.719
where we went
to that Amway meeting.

08:40.587 --> 08:42.022
Don’t let it throw you.

08:42.054 --> 08:44.558
Yeah, and remember
what I taught you last night.

08:44.591 --> 08:48.228
Never ever accept
their first offer.

08:48.261 --> 08:51.898
Even if they offer you
$50,000, you say...

08:51.932 --> 08:54.167
Fifty thousand dollars? Ha!

08:54.200 --> 08:57.170
You must be joking.

08:57.203 --> 08:59.039
‐Good.
‐Thank you.

08:59.072 --> 09:01.007
Ooh, look at this.

09:05.078 --> 09:06.913
Gentlemen, sorry
to keep you waiting.

09:06.947 --> 09:08.615
I’m J. R. Stanhouse.

09:08.649 --> 09:09.916
Senior executive vice president

09:09.950 --> 09:11.652
of Worldwide Amalgamated.

09:11.685 --> 09:14.354
In charge of corporate
acquisitions.

09:14.387 --> 09:17.791
Larry Appleton, senior executive
official adviser

09:17.824 --> 09:19.693
to the official head negotiator

09:19.726 --> 09:21.728
for the sovereign island
nation of Mypos

09:21.762 --> 09:24.030
in charge of a lot
of important stuff.

09:25.799 --> 09:27.601
Very pleased
to meet you, Mr. Appleton.

09:27.634 --> 09:29.803
And this is Balki Bartokomous

09:29.836 --> 09:31.972
official negotiator for Mypos.

09:32.005 --> 09:34.040
Mr. Bartokomous.

09:40.146 --> 09:41.314
Gentlemen, uh,
shall we get started?

09:41.347 --> 09:43.884
Oh, no, no, no.
Not‐not yet.

09:43.917 --> 09:45.218
Uh, Cousin Larry and I

09:45.251 --> 09:47.688
have to prepare the room
for the negotiations.

09:47.721 --> 09:49.756
Balki, is this really,
really necessary?

09:49.790 --> 09:51.157
Cousin, you agreed.

09:51.191 --> 09:54.595
Okay. Ah, just bear
with us for a moment.

